  "doc_id": "49607",
  "text": "Enhancing fraction (E F ) assessed using DCE-MRI or CT has been presented as a simple method of assessing whole-tumour vascularity. Enhancing fraction is the proportion of tissue within a tumour that enhances and has been shown to predict treatment outcome in ovarian [CITATION_1] and other solid tumours [CITATION_2] and has been used to assess treatment efficacy of an anti-angiogenic agent [CITATION_3] . The aim of this study was to investigate whether E F measured with DCE-MRI was able to predict treatment outcome in patients with carcinoma of the cervix.",
